      "kind": "round-trip",
      "description": "region-for-range is Excel's CurrentRegion: B2 (corner) and C3 (middle) both expand to B2:D4; F7 expands only to F6:F7 because the empty row/columns isolate the island. The gap row is what separates this from used-range above.",
      "expr": {
        "and": [
          {
            "equals": [
              {
                "$var": "regionB2"
              },
              "B2:D4"
            ]
          },
          {
